01:28.154 --> 01:30.155
Danny, $50,000 in a paper bag.

01:30.156 --> 01:31.156
This is crazy.

01:31.157 --> 01:32.658
Come on, now,

01:32.659 --> 01:33.659
we'd better rehearse the drop.

01:33.660 --> 01:35.661
You go sit down,
pretend you're us.

01:35.662 --> 01:36.662
I'll pretend I'm them.

01:36.663 --> 01:39.165
I don't have to pretend I'm us.
I am us.

01:40.667 --> 01:42.668
Well, I'm some of us.

01:42.669 --> 01:44.670
I'm part of us. I'm half of us.

01:44.671 --> 01:46.672
Go sit down.

01:46.673 --> 01:48.173
Well, we need another bag.

01:48.174 --> 01:50.176
I brought a rehearsal bag.

01:56.182 --> 01:57.683
Don't forget.

01:57.684 --> 01:59.686
Make the switch.

02:01.688 --> 02:04.190
[BOTH HUMMING]

02:21.708 --> 02:23.709
Perfect.

02:23.710 --> 02:25.711
Except one thing.
What?

02:25.712 --> 02:27.213
You took the wrong bag.

02:36.222 --> 02:38.724
You know, you are a real idiot.

02:38.725 --> 02:39.725
No one likes you.

02:39.726 --> 02:41.226
Dave likes me.

02:41.227 --> 02:43.729
Oh, yeah? Then why do you think
he's making the switch,

02:43.730 --> 02:44.730
and you're driving?

02:44.731 --> 02:45.731
The minute he gets the money,

02:45.732 --> 02:47.733
he's going to be
out the back door of the museum

02:47.734 --> 02:49.234
and off to Acapulco without you.

02:49.235 --> 02:50.236
You're nuts.

02:53.239 --> 02:54.239
Here's your lunch.

02:54.240 --> 02:55.741
What is it?
Pastrami.

02:55.742 --> 02:57.242
I hate pastrami.

02:57.243 --> 02:58.744
I hate you.

02:58.745 --> 02:59.745
Can I have your pickle?

02:59.746 --> 03:01.747
Buy your own pickle.

03:01.748 --> 03:03.749
Ready?

03:03.750 --> 03:04.750
A couple more pages.

03:04.751 --> 03:05.751
Mel, we've got
about a half-hour

03:05.752 --> 03:07.753
to get into the city
and switch the bags.

03:07.754 --> 03:08.754
Let's go.

03:08.755 --> 03:10.255
I want to make the switch.

03:10.256 --> 03:11.757
Mel, get real.

03:11.758 --> 03:14.259
You drive. I switch.
That's how we planned it.

03:14.260 --> 03:15.761
I want to pick up the money.

03:15.762 --> 03:17.262
Forget it.

03:17.263 --> 03:18.764
I don't pick up
the money, I don't go.

03:18.765 --> 03:19.765
Okay, that's it.

03:19.766 --> 03:20.767
What are you doing?

03:23.770 --> 03:25.771
Mel, the broad,
she's getting away.

03:25.772 --> 03:27.272
Stop her.

03:27.273 --> 03:28.273
Yo, lady.

03:28.274 --> 03:30.276
Stop her.

03:32.278 --> 03:33.278
[GUNSHOT]

03:33.279 --> 03:34.780
Not that way.

03:34.781 --> 03:36.783
Let's go get the money
and get out of here.

03:39.285 --> 03:40.786
Mel, forget the pickle.

03:45.792 --> 03:48.293
Want ads are so depressing.

03:48.294 --> 03:49.795
Would you like some more coffee?

03:49.796 --> 03:51.296
No, thanks,

03:51.297 --> 03:52.798
I wonder if I could be
a securities analyst.

03:52.799 --> 03:54.299
Would you like some toast?

03:54.300 --> 03:55.801
No, thanks.

03:55.802 --> 03:57.803
I wonder
what a securities analyst is.

03:57.804 --> 03:59.304
Tim, how would you like a baby?

03:59.305 --> 04:01.807
No, thanks.

04:01.808 --> 04:04.309
Tim,
you didn't hear a word I said.

04:04.310 --> 04:06.311
I'm sorry, honey,
I was looking for a job.

04:06.312 --> 04:07.312
What is it?

04:07.313 --> 04:09.815
I said,
how would you like a baby?

04:09.816 --> 04:10.816
A baby?

04:10.817 --> 04:12.818
Yeah.

04:12.819 --> 04:14.319
I'd love a baby.

04:14.320 --> 04:16.822
I really would, but later.

04:16.822 --> 04:17.822
Not now, okay?

04:17.824 --> 04:21.326
Well, I didn't mean
right this minute.

04:21.327 --> 04:23.328
It takes a little while.

04:23.329 --> 04:25.330
Honey, we'll have a baby.

04:25.331 --> 04:27.332
We'll have lots of babies,

04:27.333 --> 04:28.834
but later,
when... when I have a job,

04:28.835 --> 04:30.335
and we have our own place.

04:30.336 --> 04:32.337
That would be the time
to have a baby.

04:32.338 --> 04:33.339
Now wouldn't be.

04:37.844 --> 04:39.345
Now is.

04:41.848 --> 04:42.848
What?

04:42.849 --> 04:44.850
We're gonna have a baby.

04:44.851 --> 04:46.853
We are?

04:48.354 --> 04:50.355
We're pregnant?

04:50.356 --> 04:52.858
Well, I am.

04:52.859 --> 04:55.861
Oh, honey, that's wonderful.

04:55.862 --> 04:58.363
Sit down. Don't stand up.

04:58.364 --> 04:59.364
How do you feel?

04:59.365 --> 05:01.366
You shouldn't be drinking
coffee.

05:01.367 --> 05:02.868
God, I'm so excited. A baby.

05:02.869 --> 05:04.369
That's why you've been eating

05:04.370 --> 05:05.371
like an animal.

05:07.373 --> 05:09.875
It's a sign, honey.

05:09.876 --> 05:12.377
A baby, our own baby.

05:12.378 --> 05:13.879
Oh, boy, I can't wait.

05:13.880 --> 05:15.381
You won't really have to.

05:18.384 --> 05:19.885
A baby,

05:19.886 --> 05:21.887
we're gonna have a baby.

05:21.888 --> 05:27.392
There is just
a little something else.

05:27.393 --> 05:29.394
What?

05:29.395 --> 05:32.898
I'm... five months pregnant.

05:36.903 --> 05:37.904
Five months?

05:40.907 --> 05:42.908
Well, that would mean...

05:42.909 --> 05:43.909
Corinne.

05:43.910 --> 05:46.411
Tim, I didn't.
I swear it.

05:46.412 --> 05:48.914
There was no one,
absolutely no one.

05:48.915 --> 05:52.418
Corinne, what you're suggesting
only happened once before.

05:54.921 --> 05:57.422
Do you mean tell me that...

05:57.423 --> 05:58.423
What I mean to tell you

05:58.424 --> 06:00.926
is that I've never been
unfaithful to you.

06:00.927 --> 06:02.427
After Peter died,

06:02.428 --> 06:04.429
there was no one
until we were married.

06:04.430 --> 06:05.431
I swear it, Tim.

06:10.436 --> 06:11.937
You don't believe me.

06:11.938 --> 06:13.438
How can I?

06:13.439 --> 06:15.440
Because it's the truth.

06:15.441 --> 06:18.444
If it were reversed,
if it was me...

06:19.445 --> 06:21.446
Would you believe it?

06:21.447 --> 06:23.949
No.

06:26.953 --> 06:27.953
Tim,

06:27.954 --> 06:29.454
what are you gonna do?

06:29.455 --> 06:31.957
I don't know.

06:40.466 --> 06:41.967
Mary, Mary, we did it.

06:41.968 --> 06:43.468
They got the money,

06:43.469 --> 06:45.470
and the cops are following
the guy who picked it up.

06:45.471 --> 06:46.471
Where's Elaine?

06:46.472 --> 06:48.974
They say she'll be here
by 10:00 tonight.

06:48.975 --> 06:50.475
Oh, thank God.

06:50.476 --> 06:51.977
Did Jodie call?

06:51.978 --> 06:54.980
Yeah, he sounded okay.
He said he might drop by later.

06:54.981 --> 06:56.482
All right.

06:57.984 --> 06:59.985
Hi, guys.

06:59.986 --> 07:01.987
Hey, Bob and I
have been working on a new act.

07:01.988 --> 07:03.488
We thought
you might like to see it.

07:03.489 --> 07:05.490
Fellas, please, we're not
really in the mood now.

07:05.491 --> 07:06.992
I just kind of needed
the practice.

07:06.993 --> 07:08.493
I thought
maybe it might break the tension

07:08.494 --> 07:09.494
around here.

07:09.495 --> 07:10.996
The trick is I read minds.

07:10.997 --> 07:12.497
Oh, come on.

07:12.498 --> 07:14.499
No, it's true, come on,
Chuck, do your stuff.

07:14.500 --> 07:15.500
Okay, okay, yeah.

07:15.501 --> 07:17.503
All right, here we go.

07:19.505 --> 07:20.505
Are you ready?

07:20.506 --> 07:21.506
Ready.

07:21.507 --> 07:22.507
Okay.

07:22.508 --> 07:24.509
Danny, take something,

07:24.510 --> 07:25.510
anything.

07:25.511 --> 07:26.592
Hold it up in front of Bob.

07:34.020 --> 07:35.020
Uh...

07:35.021 --> 07:40.025
It's... round.

07:40.026 --> 07:42.027
It's...

07:42.028 --> 07:46.031
uh... glass.

07:46.032 --> 07:47.533
It's an ash tray.

07:52.538 --> 07:54.039
He's peeking.

07:54.040 --> 07:56.042
He's gotta be peeking in there.

07:57.543 --> 07:59.044
No, no, no, no,

07:59.045 --> 08:01.046
I can't see a thing,
I swear, I swear.

08:01.047 --> 08:02.047
All right, wait a minute,

08:02.048 --> 08:03.048
wait a minute.

08:03.049 --> 08:06.551
All right. Bob...

08:06.552 --> 08:07.552
What's that?

08:07.553 --> 08:09.554
Okay, okay, okay, I've got it.

08:09.555 --> 08:11.557
It's...

08:13.559 --> 08:15.560
It's... red.

08:15.561 --> 08:17.563
It's round.

08:19.065 --> 08:20.565
It's an apple.

08:20.566 --> 08:22.568
This is amazing!

08:24.570 --> 08:28.073
I don't believe this.

08:28.074 --> 08:30.075
Do know what kind of a gold mine
we've got here?

08:30.076 --> 08:31.076
Burt,

08:31.077 --> 08:34.078
Chuck can see
what you're holding up.

08:34.080 --> 08:36.082
But Bob can't.

08:39.085 --> 08:41.086
[CHUCKLING]

08:41.087 --> 08:42.587
Danny, don't you get it?

08:42.587 --> 08:44.589
No.

08:44.590 --> 08:45.590
How'd you do it?

08:45.591 --> 08:46.591
We can't tell.

08:46.592 --> 08:48.093
Oh, come on, tell me.
No, can't tell.

08:48.094 --> 08:49.094
Tell me.

08:49.095 --> 08:50.595
Hey, watch where you're going.

08:50.596 --> 08:51.596
Come on, tell me.

08:51.597 --> 08:53.598
I can't. I worked
for a long time on that.

08:53.599 --> 08:55.601
Is there a trick involved?

09:04.110 --> 09:05.611
I know, Burt.

09:07.113 --> 09:09.114
I beg your pardon?

09:09.115 --> 09:10.115
I know.

09:10.116 --> 09:11.616
You know what?

09:11.617 --> 09:14.619
I know about your affair.

09:14.620 --> 09:16.621
I know.

09:16.622 --> 09:18.123
Then you are having one?

09:18.124 --> 09:21.126
No.

09:21.127 --> 09:23.128
Burt, you've just admitted it.

09:23.129 --> 09:24.629
I admitted to knowing
that you know,

09:24.630 --> 09:27.132
but I didn't have any affair.

09:27.133 --> 09:30.135
Okay, Burt...

09:30.136 --> 09:32.137
the night you didn't come home,

09:32.138 --> 09:34.640
the night you said
a plane landed on the highway...

09:37.143 --> 09:38.643
If you are not having an affair,

09:38.644 --> 09:41.146
where were you, really,
on that night?

09:41.147 --> 09:44.149
I was...

09:44.150 --> 09:47.152
at...

09:47.153 --> 09:48.653
a woman's apartment.

09:48.654 --> 09:50.155
Oh, I hate you.

09:50.156 --> 09:52.657
Oh, so, what's this?

09:52.658 --> 09:53.658
You can, and I can't?

09:53.659 --> 09:55.160
Well, let me tell you
something, Mary.

09:55.161 --> 09:56.161
What's good for the goose,

09:56.162 --> 09:58.163
the gander can have
a hell of a good time

09:58.164 --> 09:59.664
with too.

09:59.665 --> 10:01.166
What are you talking about?

10:01.167 --> 10:02.167
Goose?

10:02.168 --> 10:03.668
I know.

10:03.669 --> 10:04.669
What?

10:04.670 --> 10:08.173
I know about you
and your professor.

10:08.174 --> 10:09.174
What about me and my professor?

10:09.175 --> 10:10.675
What about you
and your professor?

10:10.676 --> 10:11.676
Let me put it this way, Mary.

10:11.677 --> 10:16.181
Now I know why they call it
"adult" education.

10:16.182 --> 10:18.183
You're crazy.

10:18.184 --> 10:20.185
I saw you.

10:20.186 --> 10:23.188
You saw what?

10:23.189 --> 10:25.690
I came home early,
opened the door,

10:25.691 --> 10:27.692
and I saw you and your professor
on the couch

10:27.693 --> 10:29.194
going at it pretty good.

10:29.195 --> 10:31.196
He attacked me.

10:31.197 --> 10:33.198
Yeah, you didn't see me,
because you were so busy.

10:33.199 --> 10:34.699
I left, and I got drunk,

10:34.700 --> 10:36.201
and I did the same thing
you did.

10:36.202 --> 10:38.203
He attacked me.

10:38.204 --> 10:40.205
What?

10:40.206 --> 10:42.707
He attacked me,
and I threw him out.

10:42.708 --> 10:45.210
That is what you walked in on,
you big dope.

10:50.716 --> 10:51.716
An attack?

10:51.717 --> 10:53.718
Yes.

10:53.719 --> 10:56.221
Uh, not an affair, an attack?

10:56.222 --> 10:57.222
Yes.

10:57.223 --> 10:59.724
They look the same.

10:59.725 --> 11:03.228
So you mean,

11:03.229 --> 11:06.231
because of what you thought
you walked in on,

11:06.232 --> 11:08.233
you went out
and slept with someone?

11:08.234 --> 11:10.735
[CHUCKLING]

11:10.736 --> 11:12.237
No.

11:12.238 --> 11:13.738
No, I just said that

11:13.739 --> 11:15.740
so you would tell me
that you were.

11:15.741 --> 11:17.242
Burt, are you lying to me?

11:18.744 --> 11:21.246
Oh...

11:21.247 --> 11:23.748
Oh, Mary, I thought
you were having an affair.

11:23.749 --> 11:25.750
I mean, you understand me?

11:25.751 --> 11:27.752
I did it because I was hurt

11:27.753 --> 11:29.254
and angry and drunk,

11:29.255 --> 11:31.257
not because I wanted to.

11:33.759 --> 11:36.261
Uh... who is she?

11:36.262 --> 11:37.262
That's not important.

11:37.263 --> 11:38.263
I want to know.

11:38.264 --> 11:40.265
Mary, it's meaningless,
it's over.

11:40.266 --> 11:41.766
Did you have a nice time?

11:41.767 --> 11:43.268
I don't know.

11:43.269 --> 11:44.269
You don't know?

11:44.270 --> 11:46.271
I don't remember.

11:46.272 --> 11:47.272
It was one night.

11:47.273 --> 11:48.273
I don't even remember it,

11:48.274 --> 11:49.274
and I never did it again,

11:49.275 --> 11:50.775
so what difference does it make

11:50.776 --> 11:51.776
who it was?

11:53.279 --> 11:54.279
Is she skinny?

11:54.280 --> 11:56.781
Come on, Mary.

11:56.782 --> 11:59.284
I have to know that.
Is she skinny?

11:59.285 --> 12:01.286
I don't know.

12:01.287 --> 12:03.288
No, I think.

12:03.289 --> 12:05.290
I don't think she was.
I think she wasn't.

12:05.291 --> 12:06.791
In fact, I think she was obese.

12:06.792 --> 12:09.294
In fact,
I think she was grotesque.

12:11.297 --> 12:12.297
Is she young?

12:12.298 --> 12:14.799
Come on, Mary, please.

12:14.800 --> 12:17.302
She's mentioned something
about voting for Coolidge.

12:17.303 --> 12:18.304
That's...

12:21.807 --> 12:23.308
Mary, I'm sorry,

12:23.309 --> 12:24.809
but when I thought about you
and your professor,

12:24.810 --> 12:26.311
I didn't know what to do.

12:26.312 --> 12:27.312
I didn't want to do that.

12:27.313 --> 12:29.814
I wanted to die,
but I did that instead,

12:29.815 --> 12:31.316
so it's not like
I really did it.

12:31.317 --> 12:33.818
Maybe you didn't mean to do it,

12:33.819 --> 12:35.820
but you did do it.

12:35.821 --> 12:38.823
Only because I thought
you did it.

12:38.824 --> 12:40.325
You could have asked.

12:40.326 --> 12:42.327
Oh, sure, I could have come in,

12:42.328 --> 12:43.828
pulled the two of you apart,

12:43.829 --> 12:45.831
and said, "Pardon me,
are you doing it?"

12:51.837 --> 12:53.838
Mary, please, I...

12:53.839 --> 12:56.841
Look, Mary,
I only know one thing:

12:56.842 --> 12:59.844
that what we have
is more important to me

12:59.845 --> 13:01.846
than anything else in the world,

13:01.847 --> 13:02.847
and to let it end

13:02.848 --> 13:04.849
because of some dumb,
stupid mistake, Mary...

13:04.850 --> 13:06.351
That's wrong. It's a waste.

13:08.354 --> 13:09.354
Mary, please,

13:09.355 --> 13:11.357
Mary, you've got to forgive me.

13:13.359 --> 13:14.860
I'll try, Burt. I...

13:16.862 --> 13:18.864
What can I say except I'll try?

13:24.870 --> 13:27.372
I love you, Mary.

13:27.373 --> 13:29.375
I really do.

13:47.893 --> 13:49.394
[DOORBELL RINGS]

13:51.897 --> 13:54.399
[DOORBELL RINGS]

13:56.402 --> 13:57.902
You want me to get that?

13:57.903 --> 14:00.405
If you don't mind.

14:04.910 --> 14:06.911
Afternoon.
Afternoon.

14:06.912 --> 14:07.912
Detective Donohue.

14:07.913 --> 14:10.415
Hello, Mrs. Tate.

14:10.416 --> 14:11.917
No, thanks,
I'll just hold onto it.

14:13.919 --> 14:14.919
You're very late.

14:14.920 --> 14:16.921
Sorry I'm late,
but I was arrested.

14:16.922 --> 14:17.922
Arrested?

14:17.923 --> 14:19.424
Yeah. Oh, Benson,
could I get a scotch?

14:19.425 --> 14:20.425
No.

14:20.426 --> 14:23.928
Thank you...
Save my liver.

14:23.929 --> 14:24.929
Arrested?

14:24.930 --> 14:25.930
Yeah, I was walking down

14:25.931 --> 14:27.432
East 48th Street,

14:27.433 --> 14:28.933
saw a man about 6 feet tall

14:28.934 --> 14:30.435
with a bandage around his head.

14:30.436 --> 14:31.936
I was sure it was your husband.

14:31.937 --> 14:33.438
I called him to stop.

14:33.439 --> 14:35.440
He started running,
I chased after him,

14:35.441 --> 14:36.941
finally wrestled him
to the ground...

14:36.942 --> 14:38.944
Turned out to be
the ambassador from India.

14:40.946 --> 14:42.447
Detective Donohue...

14:42.448 --> 14:43.948
You can call me George.

14:43.949 --> 14:44.949
George?

14:44.950 --> 14:45.950
That's my name, George.

14:45.951 --> 14:47.452
Oh.

14:47.453 --> 14:48.453
George,

14:48.454 --> 14:49.954
this was not an easy decision

14:49.955 --> 14:50.955
to make,

14:50.956 --> 14:52.457
but I've decided to fire you.

14:52.458 --> 14:54.959
Because I was late?

14:54.960 --> 14:56.961
Boy, are you strict.

14:56.962 --> 14:58.463
I'll be on time
tomorrow, I promise.

14:58.464 --> 15:01.966
No, no, no, not because of that.

15:01.967 --> 15:04.469
It's because of the way
I feel about you, huh?

15:04.470 --> 15:07.472
Me and my big mouth.
I'd like to rip out my tongue.

15:07.473 --> 15:08.973
Of course, then,
every time I'd talk,

15:08.974 --> 15:09.974
I'd sound like an idiot.

15:09.975 --> 15:13.478
No, it's because of how I feel.

15:13.479 --> 15:15.480
Probably can't even eat
without a tongue.

15:15.481 --> 15:19.484
I feel about you
the way you feel about me.

15:19.485 --> 15:22.487
Of course, French kissing
would definitely be...

15:22.488 --> 15:24.489
What?
What'd you say?

15:24.490 --> 15:27.492
I'm afraid I feel
the same way you do.

15:27.493 --> 15:28.493
Well, that's great.

15:28.494 --> 15:29.994
No, it's terrible.

15:29.995 --> 15:32.497
It's terrible?
Why is it terrible?

15:32.498 --> 15:35.500
Because I'm married,
and I love my husband.

15:35.501 --> 15:38.503
Well, I can understand.
I mean, I can understand that.

15:38.504 --> 15:40.004
There's probably nothing
I can do.

15:40.005 --> 15:41.086
Is there anything I can do?

15:42.007 --> 15:44.008
Well, then...

15:44.009 --> 15:46.010
some other time,
some other place,

15:46.011 --> 15:47.512
some other world, whatever.

15:47.513 --> 15:49.013
Wait.
What?

15:49.014 --> 15:51.516
I just hate to see you leave.

15:51.517 --> 15:53.017
Well,
it doesn't thrill me either.

15:53.018 --> 15:55.019
I'm so confused.

15:55.020 --> 15:58.523
Do you think that it's possible
for a woman to care for two men?

15:58.524 --> 15:59.524
My mother did.

15:59.525 --> 16:00.525
She did?

16:00.526 --> 16:02.027
No, but I'll say anything
right now.

16:04.029 --> 16:07.031
You see, I have one man here
that I care for,

16:07.032 --> 16:10.034
who is actually here to look
for the other man I care for

16:10.035 --> 16:11.035
who is not here,

16:11.036 --> 16:12.537
and then, of course,

16:12.538 --> 16:14.038
I mean, if you find him,

16:14.039 --> 16:15.540
then I will have both men here

16:15.541 --> 16:16.541
that I care for,

16:16.542 --> 16:18.042
but I mean, if you leave,

16:18.043 --> 16:20.044
then I won't have
either man here,

16:20.045 --> 16:22.046
you see, that I care for.

16:22.047 --> 16:23.047
You see?

16:23.048 --> 16:25.550
Maybe.

16:25.551 --> 16:28.052
I just don't know what to do.

16:28.053 --> 16:30.054
I have a suggestion.

16:30.055 --> 16:32.557
Un-fire you?

16:32.558 --> 16:33.558
Right.

16:33.559 --> 16:35.059
Okay.

16:35.060 --> 16:37.562
I have another suggestion.

16:37.563 --> 16:39.063
What?

16:39.064 --> 16:40.064
How about a little kiss?

16:40.065 --> 16:42.067
Oh, I don't think so.

16:44.570 --> 16:46.070
Just a little peck on the cheek.

16:46.071 --> 16:47.572
Uh-uh, uh-uh, uh-uh.

16:47.573 --> 16:49.073
Just a little one.
Uh-uh.

16:49.074 --> 16:50.074
A little peck on the cheek.

16:50.075 --> 16:52.076
You won't feel a thing.

16:52.077 --> 16:53.578
It'll be like a fly landing.

17:01.587 --> 17:03.088
Okay.

17:04.589 --> 17:06.592
Nope, nothing in your ear.

17:09.555 --> 17:10.595
Benson, how about a Pepsi?

17:10.596 --> 17:12.597
No, thanks.

17:12.598 --> 17:14.098
Valuable man, Benson.

17:14.098 --> 17:16.099
I wish there were
a million more like him.

17:16.101 --> 17:17.102
There are.

17:19.605 --> 17:21.606
Would you like
to stay for dinner?

17:21.607 --> 17:22.608
Hey, that sounds like...

17:24.108 --> 17:26.611
No, I don't think so.

17:26.612 --> 17:27.612
I'll probably
just take the train,

17:27.613 --> 17:28.613
go down to the city,

17:28.614 --> 17:30.114
and get back on this case.

17:30.115 --> 17:33.618
Say, are you sure about me?

17:33.619 --> 17:34.619
Yes.

17:34.620 --> 17:35.620
Okay.

17:35.621 --> 17:37.622
Gonna find your husband.

17:37.623 --> 17:39.624
See you.

17:39.625 --> 17:40.626
See you.

17:44.630 --> 17:45.630
I beg your pardon?

17:45.631 --> 17:47.632
Sit down.

17:47.633 --> 17:48.633
What for?

17:48.634 --> 17:50.635
We've got to have a little talk.

17:50.636 --> 17:52.637
About what?

17:52.638 --> 17:54.138
About Mrs. Tate.

17:54.139 --> 17:55.640
What about her?

17:55.641 --> 17:58.142
What in the hell
do you think you're doing?

17:58.143 --> 18:00.144
Doing?

18:00.145 --> 18:02.146
Don't you think
she's been through enough

18:02.147 --> 18:03.648
without having to deal with you?

18:03.649 --> 18:05.149
I love her.

18:05.150 --> 18:07.151
Right.

18:07.152 --> 18:09.654
Hey, I don't have
to take this stuff

18:09.655 --> 18:10.655
from you.

18:10.656 --> 18:11.656
Yes, you do,

18:11.657 --> 18:12.657
and let me tell you
something else

18:12.658 --> 18:13.658
you've got to do.

18:13.659 --> 18:16.160
What's that?
Watch out for me.

18:16.161 --> 18:18.663
Because if you cause her
one moment of grief,

18:18.664 --> 18:20.164
I'm coming after you, detective.

18:20.165 --> 18:22.166
Now, let me tell you something.

18:22.167 --> 18:23.668
That woman's smile

18:23.669 --> 18:25.169
is the best thing
that's happened to me

18:25.170 --> 18:26.170
in 10 years,

18:26.171 --> 18:27.672
and if you think for one moment

18:27.673 --> 18:29.173
I'm gonna let
a little bit of grief

18:29.174 --> 18:30.174
touch that smile,

18:30.175 --> 18:31.176
you're crazy.

18:34.599 --> 18:35.680
You still want that scotch?

18:35.681 --> 18:37.682
Sure.
Good, make two.

18:37.683 --> 18:39.184
I'll have one with you.

18:56.201 --> 18:57.201
I hate waiting.

18:57.202 --> 18:58.202
Me too.

18:58.203 --> 18:59.203
So do I.

18:59.204 --> 19:00.705
For anything.

19:00.706 --> 19:02.206
[DOORBELL RINGS] It's her.

19:02.207 --> 19:03.208
It's Elaine.

19:05.711 --> 19:06.712
ALL: It's Jodie.

19:09.214 --> 19:10.715
You're that happy to see me?

19:10.716 --> 19:13.217
I'm sorry.

19:13.218 --> 19:14.218
We were waiting for Elaine.

19:14.219 --> 19:15.219
How are you?

19:15.220 --> 19:16.220
I'm fine, fine.

19:16.221 --> 19:18.222
I thought I'd come over
and wait with you.

19:18.223 --> 19:19.724
You're okay?
Yeah.

19:19.725 --> 19:20.725
You're sure?

19:20.726 --> 19:22.727
Positive.

19:22.728 --> 19:24.228
I'm a little depressed.

19:24.229 --> 19:25.229
That's what I thought.

19:25.230 --> 19:27.732
Hey, it's reasonable
to be depressed.

19:27.733 --> 19:28.733
You just got jilted.

19:28.734 --> 19:30.234
It's very depressing.

19:30.235 --> 19:31.235
Of course it is.

19:31.236 --> 19:32.737
Anyone would be
a little depressed.

19:32.738 --> 19:34.238
I'd be devastated.

19:34.239 --> 19:35.740
Actually,

19:35.741 --> 19:37.241
I'm depressed and devastated.

19:37.242 --> 19:38.242
That's normal.

19:38.243 --> 19:39.243
I mean, this thing

19:39.244 --> 19:40.745
has completely put me away, Ma.

19:40.746 --> 19:41.746
I can't stand it.

19:41.747 --> 19:43.247
I'm depressed and devastated.

19:43.248 --> 19:45.750
So how you doing, Jodie?
You feeling okay?

19:47.753 --> 19:48.753
Fine, fine.

19:48.754 --> 19:50.254
Good.

19:50.255 --> 19:52.015
Well, I'm glad to hear
you're feeling better.

19:52.758 --> 19:54.258
Listen,

19:54.259 --> 19:56.260
I... I changed
your room

19:56.261 --> 19:57.261
into a sewing room,

19:57.262 --> 19:58.763
but I'd love to change it back.

19:58.764 --> 19:59.764
I mean, I never sew,

19:59.765 --> 20:01.265
and every time I pass it,

20:01.266 --> 20:02.266
it makes me feel guilty,

20:02.267 --> 20:03.768
so why don't you move back in?

20:03.769 --> 20:05.269
I know what you're thinking.

20:05.270 --> 20:06.771
That I wouldn't have to sew.

20:06.772 --> 20:09.273
It'd be wonderful.
I hate sewing.

20:09.274 --> 20:10.775
I'm not gonna kill myself.

20:10.776 --> 20:12.276
Did I say that?

20:12.277 --> 20:15.279
Did you hear me say
anything about killing?

20:15.280 --> 20:16.781
I mentioned sewing, not killing.

20:16.782 --> 20:18.282
Ma, I'm gonna be okay.

20:18.283 --> 20:19.283
I promise,

20:19.284 --> 20:21.786
I'm not gonna kill myself.

20:21.787 --> 20:24.288
[DOORBELL RINGS]

20:24.289 --> 20:25.289
Elaine.

20:25.290 --> 20:26.290
I made it.

20:26.291 --> 20:27.792
Elaine.

20:27.793 --> 20:29.794
Oh, God, she's been shot.

20:29.795 --> 20:31.295
I'll call an ambulance.

20:31.296 --> 20:32.296
I made it.

20:32.297 --> 20:33.798
I'm home.

20:33.799 --> 20:37.802
Shh, don't talk, babe.
Save your strength.

20:37.803 --> 20:39.303
I love you, Danny.

20:39.304 --> 20:40.805
Do you know that I love you?

20:40.806 --> 20:41.806
I know.

20:41.807 --> 20:42.807
Do you really know?

20:42.808 --> 20:44.809
Yes. Now, don't talk.
Please, rest.

20:44.810 --> 20:46.310
You have made me so happy.

20:46.311 --> 20:47.812
Shh, shh.

20:47.813 --> 20:49.313
I had to get back to tell you.

20:49.314 --> 20:51.315
I didn't want to die
without telling you.

20:51.316 --> 20:53.818
You're not dying, Elaine,
you're not dying.

20:53.819 --> 20:56.320
Do something, somebody,
please, do something!

20:56.321 --> 20:57.321
I've called the ambulance.

20:57.322 --> 20:59.824
They'll get here
as soon as they can.

20:59.825 --> 21:02.326
Thank you, Burt.

21:02.327 --> 21:05.329
It's all right, it's all right.

21:05.330 --> 21:06.831
It's all right.

21:06.832 --> 21:08.833
I love you, Elaine.

21:08.834 --> 21:10.334
I love you. Do you know that?

21:10.335 --> 21:11.335
Yes.

21:11.336 --> 21:12.837
I've always loved you.

21:12.838 --> 21:13.838
Not always.

21:13.839 --> 21:15.840
Always, always.

21:15.841 --> 21:19.343
Even when you called me "yutz."
Even then I loved you.

21:19.344 --> 21:20.845
I never meant it.

21:20.846 --> 21:21.846
I know.

21:21.847 --> 21:25.349
I know, silly.

21:25.350 --> 21:26.851
I know.

21:26.852 --> 21:30.354
Don't be sad, Danny.

21:30.355 --> 21:31.856
I don't want you to be sad.

21:33.859 --> 21:34.859
Don't talk.

21:34.860 --> 21:35.860
Please, Elaine,

21:35.861 --> 21:37.361
save your strength,
save your strength.

21:37.362 --> 21:39.864
Because it's all right.

21:39.865 --> 21:42.366
It's all right.

21:42.367 --> 21:44.368
I'm home.

21:44.369 --> 21:46.871
You've got to save
your strength, Elaine.

21:46.872 --> 21:49.373
Shh.

21:49.374 --> 21:51.375
Shh.

21:51.376 --> 21:54.378
Don't talk, don't talk.

21:54.379 --> 21:56.881
I'll talk. Let me talk.

21:56.882 --> 21:58.883
I love you.

21:58.884 --> 22:00.885
I love you, and you're home now,

22:00.886 --> 22:03.387
and you're gonna be fine.

22:03.388 --> 22:05.389
I promise, Elaine,
you're gonna be fine,

22:05.390 --> 22:08.893
you're gonna be just fine.

22:11.897 --> 22:14.899
I am fine...

22:14.900 --> 22:16.401
now.

22:18.403 --> 22:20.905
You're gonna be fine, Elaine.

22:20.906 --> 22:24.408
You've got to be.
You've got to be.

22:24.409 --> 22:27.412
Please, please, please, be fine.

22:31.917 --> 22:33.418
Elaine?

22:39.424 --> 22:40.425
Elaine.

22:47.432 --> 22:50.935
It's all right now, Elaine.

22:50.936 --> 22:52.437
It's all right.

22:54.940 --> 22:57.943
You're home.

